answers.body_markdown:
Assuming server returns data using `text/event-stream` media type, you can consume stream using `WebClient` and then emit as a `Flux`.


```
@GetMapping(path = &quot;/client&quot;, produces = TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)
Flux&lt;String&gt; client() {
        return webclient.post()
                .uri(&quot;/server&quot;)
                .accept(MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM)
                .header(HttpHeaders.CONNECTION, &quot;keep-alive&quot;)
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToFlux(String.class);
}
```

You can test it by simulating server events from the same controller

```
@PostMapping(path = &quot;/server&quot;, produces = TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)
Flux&lt;String&gt; server() {
    return Flux.interval(Duration.ofSeconds(1))
         .map(i -&gt; &quot;value-&quot; + i);
}
```

Here is a `curl` command to validate
```
curl -v -H &quot;Accept: text/event-stream&quot; http://localhost:8080/client

